pan><span class=\"n\">y₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y₂</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rq_rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RqFromRule</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">RqFromRule</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RqFromRule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y₂</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rq_rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Are there any pros and cons for using one versus the other? Structures for instance might require some <code>⟨...⟩</code> unpacking and repacking while inductive types bring in their own syntax overhead. Are there any significant advantages of either method you could recommend?</p>",
