    {
        "content": "<p><code>structure</code>s <em>are</em> inductive types + some additional functions. In other words, everything you'd find from inductive types (<code>Rq.mk</code>, matches) are present on structures and most things from structures (<code>.1</code>, <code>⟨x⟩</code>) are also present on inductive types of the right shape. So, since structures are just strictly more than inductives (bringing the <code>{ val := _ }</code> syntax and projection functions), I'd just go with structures.</p>",
